HEADWORD: Cauliculus
<hw>Cau*lic"u*lus</hw> <pr>(k⟦add⟧*l⟦icr⟧k"⟦usl⟧*l⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Cauliculi</plw>
<pr>(-l⟦imac⟧)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>cauliculus</ets> little stalk,
dim. of <ets>caulis</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>In the
Corinthian capital, one of the eight stalks rising out of the lower
leafage and terminating in leaves which seem to support the volutes. See
<er>Illust</er>. of <er>Corinthian order</er>, under
<er>Corinthian</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

